A variety of open-source and commercial tools can assist in metadata extraction. Familiarity with several will prove invaluable.

    ExifTool: A powerful, cross-platform command-line tool that supports reading, writing, and editing metadata in a vast array of file formats. It's the industry standard for comprehensive metadata analysis.
    bash

    # Extract all metadata from an image
    exiftool image.jpg

    # Extract specific fields
    exiftool -GPSLatitude -GPSLongitude -CreateDate image.jpg

